<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,824,959]" box="[151,1267,824,851]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,825,851]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described based on a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1025,824,850]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1040,1254,824,850]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,824,959]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">
Currently it is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[504,599,860,886]" name="Ecuador" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[610,664,861,887]" name="Peru" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[675,757,860,886]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[772,900,861,887]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[919,987,860,886]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1002,1119,860,887]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1130,1296,860,887]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[289,400,896,922]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[416,524,897,923]" country="Argentina" name="Tucuman" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">Tucumán</collectingRegion>
) (Bezark 2022; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[708,855,897,923]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" refId="ref5080" refString="Monne, M. A. (2022) Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part II. Subfamily Lamiinae. Available from: https: // cerambycids. com / catalog / (accessed 22 April 2022.)" type="url" year="2022">Monné 2022</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; Chevillotte, H." box="[866,1214,896,923]" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" refId="ref5126" refString="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2021) Titan: base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 23 April 2022.)" type="url" year="2021">Tavakilian &amp; Chevillotte 2021</bibRefCitation>
). This geographical distribution suggests that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1920" box="[438,677,932,959]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subreticulatus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[438,463,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[479,503,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[519,677,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">subreticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bruch" authorityYear="1911" box="[953,1158,933,959]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spegazzinii" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[953,977,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[993,1017,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1034,1158,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="102">spegazzinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
